JDK Download link(JDK 17): 
---------------
https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/#jdk17-windows


1) Download and install Java(JDK)
2) Set Java Path/ Class path
	Set Java path: C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-17\bin

Command to verify java installation
------------
java -version


IDE - Integrated Development Environment
----
Eclipse
Java Beans
Intellij Idea
etc.....

Eclipse Download link: https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/


1) Create a new Java project ( File-->New--Java Project)
2) create a new java package ( right click on src-->package) 
3) create a new class( right click on package-->new -->class)

Naming convensions
----
1) Class name should start with Uppercase
2) Class name should not start with number
3) Class name contains _  ( Underscore)
4) Special characters are not allowed
5) class name contains number/s


Ctrl  = CMD
Syso --> Ctrl +space(CMD+Space)

// single line comment
/*    */    multi line comment



Crtl+Shift+/    multi line comment
Ctrl+/    single line comment


*****************************************Day 2 - lecture******************************************
Variables and Data types
-----------------------
Variable is a container which can hold data.
to represent data we need variables.

int x=100
int age=30
float price=150.50
double price=150.50
String name="John"
char grad='A'

Data types
-----------
Data type represents type of data.

1) Premitive

byte, short, int, long -----> number without decimal
float, double ------> decimal number
char   --------> single character (single quote)
boolean   ---> true/false


2) Non-premitive/ Derived /Collections
String
ArrayList
HashMap
HashSet
Object
etc......

DataType	Size			Description
--------------------------------------------------
byte		1 byte			Stores whole numbers from -128 to 127

short		2 bytes	    		Stores whole numbers from -32,768 to 32,767
int		4 bytes			Stores whole numbers from -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647
long		8 bytes			Stores whole numbers from -9,223,372,036,854,775,808 to 9,223,372,036,854,775,807

float		4 bytes		   Stores fractional numbers. Sufficient for storing 7 decimal digits
double		8 bytes		   Stores fractional numbers. Sufficient for storing 15 decimal digits

boolean		1 bit		      	Stores true or false values
char		2 bytes			Stores a single character/letter


char ch='ABC';  // invalid
String ch='ABC'    // invalid

String ch='A'     // invalid
String ch="A"     // valid


boolean b=true;   //valid
boolean b="true"   // invalid

String s=true;   // not valid

String s="true";  // valid









































